Iavan Pijoos, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - An alleged cop killer was arrested after he shot a police officer in the head, Ekurhuleni metro police said on Wednesday.The 33-year-old man is wanted for several police killings.He was expected to appear in the Vosloorus Magistrate's Court on Wednesday.Three men robbed a shop at Chris Hani Mall of an undisclosed amount of cash and several cellphones on Tuesday.&nbsp; When they exited the shop they saw a police officer in uniform in an unmarked vehicle, Lieutenant Colonel Wilfred Kgasago said.&nbsp;"The robbers thought that the officer was responding to the incident," Kgasago said.&nbsp; &nbsp; Two of the men fled the scene, while the third suspect shot the police officer in the head. He survived and was taken to a nearby hospital.&nbsp;Kgasago said a security guard called metro police to the scene.Police managed to arrest the suspect in a nearby field. &nbsp;The other two men were still at large.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.